{
  "bookId": "laozi-wangbi-wiki",
  "num": 34,
  "title": "第三十四章",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "大道氾兮，其可左右。"
    },
    {
      "text": "萬物恃之而生而不辭，功成不名有。衣養萬物而不為主，常無欲，可名於小；"
    },
    {
      "text": "萬物歸焉而不為主，可名為大。"
    },
    {
      "text": "以其終不自為大，故能成其大。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言道氾濫，無所不適，可左右上下周旋而用，則無所不至也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 34
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "萬物皆由道而生，既生而不知所由，故天下常無欲之時，萬物各得其所，若道無施於物，故名於小矣。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 14
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "萬物皆歸之以生，而力使不知其所由，此不為小，故復可名於大矣。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 14
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "為大於其細，圖難於其易。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
